issue.title: CatBoost can't handle both silent and verbose switches.

repository.name: hyperparameter_hunter
repository.description: Easy hyperparameter optimization and automatic result saving across machine learning algorithms and libraries

issue.body:
Using catboost==0.9.1.1. When used in 
```python
    experiment = CrossValidationExperiment(
        model_initializer=CatBoostRegressor,
        model_init_params=dict(iterations=10, learning_rate=0.01, depth=7, allow_writing_files=False),
        model_extra_params=dict()  # Send kwargs to `fit` and other extra methods
    )
```
it breaks down with
```
_catboost.CatboostError: Only one of the parameters silent and verbose should be set
```

body: @alaneckhardt, this is being reopened due to problems mentioned in #80, outlined [here](https://github.com/HunterMcGushion/hyperparameter_hunter/issues/80#issuecomment-425300120).
